                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription is dated in the same year and month, as No. 86, and during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kambaṇa-uḍaiyar</hi>, the son of <hi rend="bold">Vīra</hi>. It records that, with the sanction of <hi rend="bold">Kopaṇṇaṅgaḷ,</hi><note n="120-4">See page 118, above.</note> the authorities of the <hi rend="bold">Rājasiṁhavarmeśvara</hi> Temple at <hi rend="bold">Kāñchipuram</hi> sold some houses in the northern row of the <hi rend="italic">saṁnidhi</hi> street to certain <hi rend="italic">Mudalis</hi> at the price of 150 <hi rend="italic">paṇas</hi>.</p>						
                            
